item.description:
Getting the unique serial number from a Raspberry Pi.
cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep ^Serial | cut -d&quot;:&quot; -f2  Example output:
 00000000e215b4a2  An interesting use for this is &ldquo;binding&rdquo; software, encryption or other servcies to a specific Pi. Found this in a suggestion on the Stack Overflow question &ldquo;Securing data on SD card Raspberry Pi&rdquo;
